Nexus Engineering S.r.l., in consortium with specialized partners including EuroCloud Solutions S.A., LexIA GmbH, and GreenCompute S.r.l., proposes a comprehensive artificial intelligence (AI) solution to assist municipal agents of the City of Belval in their daily administrative activities. Our solution integrates cutting-edge technologies, ensures strict compliance with regulatory requirements such as GDPR, and prioritizes sustainability while enhancing performance.

### Understanding of Requirements
The City of Belval seeks an AI-powered assistance tool for its municipal agents to improve efficiency, facilitate access to information, enhance the quality of responses, and reduce processing times. The solution must integrate with existing systems, ensure high availability, respect sovereignty constraints, and adhere to a budget of 3 million euros over four years.

### Proposed Solution
Our proposed solution leverages Mistral 7B, our preferred sovereign LLM model, fine-tuned using LoRA and QLoRA methods to adapt to the client's specific needs. The Retrieval-Augmented Generator (RAG) capabilities utilize dense vector semantic search and recursive text splitter chunking strategies to provide relevant information and suggest actions within administrative processes. Explainability tools like source citation, chain-of-thought display, and SHAP for classification models ensure transparent and trustworthy suggestions.

For integration with existing systems, we will employ API gateways like Kong and Apigee, supporting REST, GraphQL, and SOAP standards. Electronic document management systems such as Alfresco and OpenKM will be integrated, along with identity providers like Active Directory and Keycloak for user directory integration.

Our hosting solution will utilize SecNumCloud or equivalent infrastructure within the EU, ensuring data sovereignty and compliance with GDPR. We guarantee a high level of availability, targeting 99.92%, and response times optimized to meet the requirement of less than 2 seconds.

From a legal standpoint, we ensure compliance with GDPR through our Data Protection Agreement (DPA) template version 3.2, reliance on Article 6(1)(e) as the standard legal basis for processing, and support for Data Protection Impact Assessments (DPIAs). Our intellectual property model is based on a work-for-hire approach, minimizing risks related to IP ownership.

Our budget approach ensures that we are within the client's estimated global budget of 3 million euros. With a maximum contract value eligibility threshold of 3,000,000 euros and a target gross margin percentage of 28%, we aim to optimize costs while guaranteeing quality of service.

Sustainability is a core aspect of our proposal. With an EcoVadis rating of Silver (score of 62) and a net-zero target for 2040, we prioritize environmental impact reduction. Our green hosting partners, OVHcloud and Scaleway, use 100% renewable energy and are ISO14001 certified. Digital sobriety measures such as model quantization and auto-scaling result in a typical energy reduction of 35%.

### Unaddressed Requirements
While our proposal addresses the majority of the requirements outlined by the City of Belval, specific details on managing the annual cost of exploitation to remain compatible with the local authority's budgetary capacities are not fully elaborated due to limitations in the provided context. Additionally, exact figures for costs and revenues associated with this project that would allow for the calculation of an exact projected margin are not specified.

### Conclusion
Nexus Engineering S.r.l., along with its consortium partners, is committed to delivering a cutting-edge AI solution that meets the City of Belval's needs while prioritizing regulatory compliance, sustainability, and performance. With our expertise in public sector projects, AI innovation, security, legal compliance, budget management, and CSR & sustainability, we are confident in our ability to provide an effective and responsible solution for the municipal agents of Belval.
